5. THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
================================================================================

The Software incorporates third-party libraries and assets distributed under
their own licenses. Those components remain subject to their respective
licenses and are not relicensed under this license.

Authoritative list — the .csproj files in the source repository
(https://github.com/Oriinks/LYNXCommander-public) are the canonical source of
truth for current dependency versions. As of the version of this license,
the following NuGet packages are used:

  Overlay (LynxOverlay.csproj):
    - .NET 8 Windows runtime (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - Microsoft.Windows.SDK.NET (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - NAudio (Mark Heath et al., MIT)
    - MumbleSharp (Martin Evans, MIT)
    - Concentus (Logan Stromberg, MIT — managed C# port of libopus)
    - Velopack (Caelan Sayler / Velopack contributors, MIT)
    - Microsoft.Web.WebView2 (Microsoft Corporation, BSD-style)
    - Microsoft.AspNetCore.SignalR.Client (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - System.IdentityModel.Tokens.Jwt (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - Serilog, Serilog.Sinks.File, Serilog.Sinks.Console,
      Serilog.Enrichers.Process, Serilog.Enrichers.Thread (Serilog
      Contributors, Apache 2.0)

  Backend (LynxApi.csproj):
    - .NET 8 ASP.NET Core runtime (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - System.IdentityModel.Tokens.Jwt (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore + EntityFrameworkCore.Design
      (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)
    - Pomelo.EntityFrameworkCore.MySql (Pomelo Foundation, MIT)
    - AspNet.Security.OAuth.Discord (.NET Foundation, Apache 2.0)
    - zeroc.ice.net (ZeroC Inc., GPLv2 with Linking Exception — Mumble
      management interface bridge only)

  Installer (LynxInstaller.csproj):
    - .NET 8 Windows runtime (Microsoft Corporation, MIT)

Star Citizen and Roberts Space Industries are trademarks of Cloud
Imperium Games Corp. The Software is an unofficial third-party tool
and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Cloud Imperium
Games.

This list is provided in good faith and may lag minor dependency version
bumps; the .csproj files in the repository are always the most accurate
source.

